Bungoma nurses suspended their strike, which was to start on Thursday. Speaking to the press at a Bungoma hotel, Kenya National Union of Nurses Bungoma branch secretary general George Musundi said on Thursday the county has partly met their demands and they have been assured by Health executive Stephen Kokonya the remaining issues will be resolved as soon as possible .Musundi said the Bungoma Public Service Board had issued letters of promotions to more than 100 health workers. He said if the county fails to promote the remaining 230 workers after 21 days, they will go on strike.He urged workers to remain on duty until September 15. Musundi said Kokonya has agreed with Kemsa to fast-track delivery of medical equipment and that drugs before the end of this month. He added that members of the Public Service Board were to be blame for the delayed promotions.